  "market_context": "August 7, intraday session. Market structure showed lower low and break of structure to downside. Analyst focused on New York session opening (06:30 AM NY) as catalyst for liquidity sweep above prior swing highs and Asia/London ranges.",
  "key_observation": "Price had formed a bearish market structure with a recent lower low; a fair value gap (FVG) from a range-aggression sequence served as the key point of interest where price was expected to react after liquidity sweep.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify directional bias — confirmed bearish via lower low and break of structure on 15M chart, establishing only short trades were considered.",
    "Step 2: Identify point of interest — located a range followed by aggressive downward move; the gap between low of first candle and high of third candle formed a fair value gap (FVG), marked as POI.",
    "Step 3: Identify retail liquidity — mapped Asia session high, London session high, equal highs, and trendline liquidity above current price; anticipated New York session would trigger long bias and stop-loss sweeps there.",
    "Step 4: Wait for manipulation and mitigation — expected price to sweep above liquidity (BSL) before reversing into the FVG POI.",
    "Step 5: Drop to 1-minute timeframe for confirmation — waited for bearish shift (e.g., break of 1M low or push-up/pullback/push-down pattern) to confirm sellers in control before entry.",
    "Step 6: Enter short with tight stop — placed entry near FVG POI (~1.27140), stop loss just above swing high (~1.27270), targeting liquidity at prior lows (~1.26800)."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade entered short near 1.27140, stop at ~1.27270 (6-pip), took partial profit at 1:5 RR and full at ~1:8.27 RR; price moved down to target liquidity zone below 1.26800, confirming trade success.",
  "lessons": "Successful short required aligning bearish market structure, FVG POI, and time-based liquidity (NY session). Entry only after 1M bearish shift ensured high-probability timing and tight risk, maximizing reward.",
